7.2 Separate Insurance.
Except for the coverages to be procured and maintained by the Administrative Owner with respect to the Common Facilities pursuant to Section 7.1, each of the Parties, at its sole cost and expense, shall maintain property, liability and other insurance coverages on its Project as required by the terms of any Shared Real Property Document or as otherwise necessary in order to adhere to Prudent Industry Practices. The Parties shall provide evidence of this insurance coverage (including copies of policies) to each other on written request, and, if required, to Landowners pursuant to the Shared Real Property Documents.
ARTICLE 8 : TRANSFER OF INTERESTS; LIENS
8.1 Restrictions on Transfer.
No Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its Ownership Interest or other rights or interests in or to the Common Facilities, or in, to or under this Agreement, without (i) assigning or transferring such Common Facilities and Agreement rights and interests together to the same assignee, such that the Common Facilities are not separated in ownership from the rights and interests under this Agreement, and (ii) obtaining the prior written consent of all other Owners, except that such consent shall not be required for a sale, assignment or transfer by an Owner (a Transferring Party), in the following circumstances:
(a) if the purchaser, assignee or transferee is an entity with which the Transferring Party has consolidated or into which the Transferring Party has merged or which acquires by conveyance, transfer or lease all or substantially all of the assets of such Transferring Party and such purchaser, assignee, lessee or assignee shall have agreed with the other Owners, in writing, to unconditionally assume, on a recourse basis, the due and punctual performance and observance of all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement;
(b) the assignee or transferee of an Owners Ownership Interest in the Common Facilities is the holder of any debt, equity or obligation of such Transferring Party and the assignment or transfer of such Transferring Party is pursuant to the terms of a mortgage, trust, security agreement, indenture or other instrument of indebtedness to which the Transferring Party and such holder of debt, equity or obligation (or such trustee) (a Lender) are parties, in the nature of a lien, security interest or collateral assignment (each a Lenders Lien) as security for any indebtedness of the Transferring Party, past or future; or
(c) the assignment or transfer is pursuant to the acquisition of all or a part of an Owners Ownership Interest in the Common Facilities as part of an acquisition of such Owners rights, title and interest in all or a portion of its project and such acquirer shall have agreed with the other Owners, in writing, to unconditionally assume, on a recourse basis, the due and punctual performance and observance of all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement. The non-assigning or non-transferring Owner may require as a condition of any such transfer such approval under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act for any related disposition of FERC-jurisdictional assets, and any acceptance by FERC under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act of any amendments of this Agreement or any agreements related to assignment or assumption of interests under this Agreement, or any concurrences or tariff records made by an Owner in conformity with FERCs regulations. If the transfer is for a portion of its Project, then such Owner shall determine whether such new Owner would have representation on the Owners Committee through the allocation of one or two of such Owners members. However, the other Owners number of members shall remain unaffected by such transfer and the total number of members on the Owners Committee shall remain four, unless unanimously agreed by the parties.
Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, no Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its interest in the Common Facilities or under this Agreement to any entity with which any other Owner is barred by applicable law from holding an undivided interest in the Common Facilities or under this Agreement.
8.2 Transfer Requirements.
No sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Common Facilities pursuant to Section 8.1 above, or which requires the consent of the other Owners, may be made by any Owner unless simultaneously such Owners rights in, to and under this Agreement that relate to such interest are similarly sold, assigned or transferred to the same Person or Persons, and such Person or Persons have assumed in writing all of the duties and obligations under this Agreement of the Owner making such sale, assignment or transfer that relate to such interest. Any such sale, assignment or transfer (i) shall relieve an Owner of any future obligation under this Agreement, provided that the transferee agrees in writing to assume all such obligations, and (ii) shall relieve an Owner of any past obligation under this Agreement only to the extent consented to in writing by the other Owners. No Owner may transfer all or part of its rights to use the Common Facilities separately from its Project. Any attempted or purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Common Facilities or this Agreement made other than in accordance with this Article 8 either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect. Administrative Owner will notify FirstEnergy in writing, within thirty (30) calendar days, of any transfer of Ownership Interest or other rights or interests in the Common Facilities under this Agreement.
8.3 Succession as Owner.
Any permitted purchaser, assignee or transferee (other than an assignee of a security interest pursuant to Section 8.1(b) prior to foreclosure thereon) shall be considered an Owner and Party for purposes of this Agreement.
8.4 Lender Protection.
(a) Parties Obligations. Each Party agrees to consent to financing documents as may reasonably be required by Lenders. As a precondition to exercising any remedies related to any alleged default by a Party under this Agreement, any other Party shall give notice of the default to each Lender at the same time it delivers notice of the default to the first Party, specifying in detail the alleged default and the required remedy. Each Lender shall have the same amount of time to cure the default as is given to the first Party and the same right to cure any default as the first Party. The cure period for each Lender shall begin to run at the end of the cure period given to Parties in this Agreement, but in no case shall the cure period for any Lender be less than thirty (30) calendar days after receipt of the notice of default. The Lender shall have the absolute right to substitute itself for the first Party and perform the duties of the first Party hereunder for purposes of curing such default. Each Party expressly consents to such substitution, agrees to accept such performance and authorizes the Lender (or its employees, agents, representatives or contractors) to enter upon the Common Facilities to complete such performance with all of the rights and privileges of the first Party hereunder.
(b) Lender Obligations. Any Lender that does not directly hold an interest under this Agreement, or whose interest is held solely for security purposes, shall have no obligation or liability to any other Party for performance of a Partys obligations under this Agreement prior to the time the Lender directly holds an interest in this Agreement, or succeeds to absolute title to a Partys interest. A Lender shall be liable to perform obligations of a Party to the other Parties under this Agreement only for and during the period it directly holds such interest. Any assignment permitted under this Agreement shall release a Party or other assignor from obligations accruing after the date that liability is assumed by a transferee, but the assigning Party shall continue to be liable to the other Parties for all performance due by the assigning Party for matters that have accrued and are unsatisfied as of the date of the assignment. Further in the event that a Lender elects to (i) perform a Partys obligations under this Agreement, (ii) acquire any portion of a Partys right, title or interest in all or any of the Common Facilities or (iii) enter into a new agreement as provided in Section 8.4(f), then such Lender shall not have any personal liability to a Party in connection therewith, and a non-defaulting Partys sole recourse in the event of a default by such Lender shall be to execute against such Lenders interest in the Common Facilities. Moreover, any Lender or other Person who acquires an interest in the Common Facilities pursuant to foreclosure or an assignment in lieu of foreclosure shall not be liable to perform any obligations under the Agreement to the extent the same are incurred or accrue after such Lender or other Person no longer has ownership of such interest.
(c) Lenders Right to Possession, Right to Acquire and Right to Assign. A Lender shall have the absolute right: (i) to assign its Lenders Lien; (ii) to enforce its Lenders Lien and acquire title to the applicable interest in the Common Facilities by any lawful means; and (iii) to perform all obligations to be performed by a Party under this Agreement, or to cause a receiver to be appointed to do so. No Partys consent shall be required for any of the foregoing, and upon acquisition of an interest in the Common Facilities by a Lender or any other third party who acquires the same from or on behalf of the Lender, a Party shall recognize the Lender or such other party (as the case may be) as the other Partys proper successor, and this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect.
(d) Opportunity to Cure. Following acquisition of an interest in the Common Facilities by the Lender as a result of either foreclosure or acceptance of an assignment in lieu of foreclosure, or by a purchaser at a foreclosure sale, this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect and the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Common Facilities shall, as promptly as reasonably possible, commence the cure of all defaults under this Agreement and thereafter diligently process such cure to completion; provided, however, that the Lender or party acquiring title to such interest in the Common Facilities shall not be required to cure those defaults which are not reasonably susceptible of being cured or performed by such party. If a Lender is prohibited by any process or injunction issued by any court or by reason of any action of any court having jurisdiction over any bankruptcy or insolvency proceeding involving the defaulting Party from commencing or prosecuting the appropriate judicial or non-judicial proceedings, then any cure period for commencing such proceedings shall be extended for the period of such prohibition.
(e) Termination. Neither the bankruptcy nor the insolvency of a Party shall be grounds for terminating this Agreement as long as all payments and all other monetary charges payable by the Party under this Agreement are paid by the Lender in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.
(f) New Agreement. In the event that this Agreement is rejected or disaffirmed pursuant to bankruptcy law or any other law affecting creditors rights, then, so long as a Lender has cured any such monetary default and is making commercially reasonable efforts to cure any such non-monetary default as provided herein, the non-defaulting Party(ies) shall, immediately upon request from such Lender received within ninety (90) calendar days after any such event, without demanding additional consideration therefore, enter into a shared use agreement with such Lender, which new shared use agreement shall (i) contain the same covenants, agreements, terms, provisions and limitations as this Agreement (except for any requirements that have been fulfilled by the Parties prior to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance), and (ii) be for a term commencing on the date of such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance and continuing for the remaining term of this Agreement before giving effect to such termination, foreclosure, rejection or disaffirmance. At the option of the Lender, the new shared use agreement may be executed by a designee of such Lender, with the Lender assuming the burdens and obligations of the defaulting Party thereunder. If more than one Lender makes a request for a new shared use agreement pursuant hereto, then the same shall be delivered to the Lender whose lien is senior in priority.
(g) Lender Consent. Notwithstanding any provision of this Agreement to the contrary, (i) a Party shall not agree to a modification or amendment of this Agreement if the same could reasonably be expected to materially reduce the rights or remedies of a Lender or impair or reduce the security for a Lenders Lien, and (ii) a Party shall not accept a termination of this Agreement without the prior consent of each Lender.
(h) Further Assurances. The Owners, the Administrative Owner and the Owners Committee shall exercise commercially reasonable efforts, at their own cost and expense, to (i) cooperate in amending this Agreement from time to time to include any provision that may be reasonably requested by any Lender to preserve a Lenders Lien, and (ii) execute any documents which may reasonably be required by a Lender to give effect to a provision of this Agreement.
ARTICLE 9 : DEFAULT AND REMEDIES
9.1 Demand for Payment or Performance.
Upon failure of an Owner to make or cause to be made any payment when due and owing, or to perform or cause to be performed any other obligation to be performed by it, pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the other Owners may make written demand upon said Owner for such payment or performance.
9.2 Payment Defaults.
If an Owner fails to make or cause to be made a payment when due and owing pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement or in any Shared Real Property Document, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within ten (10) Business Days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 9.1, such failure shall, upon the expiration of such ten (10) working day period, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement; provided, however, that if such payment is timely made under protest pursuant to Section 9.1, a default by such Owner with respect to such payment shall not be deemed to have occurred.
9.3 Performance Defaults.
If an Owner fails to perform or cause to be performed any obligation (other than a payment obligation) to be performed by it pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement or in any Shared Real Property Document, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within thirty (30) days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 9.1, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said thirty (30) day period, within a reasonable period following the date on which such Owner receives such demand, such failure shall, upon the expiration of the applicable grace period pursuant to this Section 9.3, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement; provided, however, that if such obligation is timely performed under protest pursuant to this Section 9.3, a default by such Owner with respect to performance of such obligation shall not be deemed to have occurred.
9.4 Disputed Defaults.
If an Owner disputes a default asserted against it by written demand pursuant to Section 9.1, then such Owner may make or cause to be made payment of any sums in dispute or perform the obligation in dispute under protest and without prejudice to any rights or remedies that such Owner may have pursuant to any of this Agreement or in any Shared Real Property Document or at law or in equity. The Owner purportedly in default shall (i) deliver such protest in writing to each Owner making demand with respect thereto, (ii) specify in such protest the reasons upon which the protest is based and (iii) deliver a copy of such protest to each non-demanding Owner in accordance with the notice provisions of Section 12.1. If such dispute is resolved in favor of the Owner upon whom demand was made, the Owner making demand upon such Owner shall, by means of appropriate adjustment of amounts payable by the Owners respectively pursuant to any of this Agreement, reimburse to such Owner the amount of any payments made under rightful protest and the amount of the costs and expenses incurred by such Owner in performing any obligation under rightful protest, each such reimbursement to be made, together with interest thereon at the Interest Rate, such interest to accrue from (and including) the date such payments were made or performance accomplished under rightful protest to (but excluding) the date of such reimbursement.
9.5 Interest on Late Payments.
Any payment not made by a defaulting Owner when due and owing pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement may be advanced by any other Owner and, if so advanced, the amount of such payments shall be repayable to such other Owners by the defaulting Owner with interest at the Interest Rate, such interest to accrue from (and including) the date such advance is made to (but excluding) the date of repayment of such advance by the defaulting Owner.
9.6 Remedies Cumulative.
The remedies available pursuant to this Article 9 shall be in addition to and not in lieu of other remedies available to the non-defaulting Owner pursuant to this Agreement or at law or in equity, and the exercise of remedies pursuant to this Article 9 shall not release the defaulting Owner from any of its obligations under this Agreement. In addition to exercising the rights granted in this Article 9, any non-defaulting Owner may exercise any right or remedy or take any action available to such non-defaulting Owner, at law or in equity, including bringing an action for specific performance to enforce this Agreement or to cure any defaults by the other Owner under a Shared Real Property Document and to recover for any loss, damage or payment advances, including reasonable attorneys fees, in all trial and appellate courts and collection costs incurred by reason of the default of any Owner.
9.7 Existing Liens Not Affected.
No remedy or action taken pursuant to this Article 9 by a non-defaulting Owner in connection with a default by another Owner is intended to give rise to the creation of any lien, claim or encumbrance of any non-defaulting Owner that is prior to the lien, claim or encumbrance of any secured party under any mortgage, loan, credit agreement or other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness between such secured party and such defaulting Owner existing as of the occurrence of such default by such defaulting Owner, except to the extent permitted under such mortgage, loan, credit agreement, other security agreement or instrument of indebtedness.
9.8 Separate Defaults.
Each act or omission to act that constitutes a default under this Agreement shall be treated as a separate default under this Article 9.
ARTICLE 10 : DISPUTE RESOLUTION
10.1 Owners Representatives.
In addition to its members on the Owners Committee, each Owner shall appoint one (1) representative (who may also be a member on the Owners Committee) to coordinate with the other Owner the performance of this Agreement (each a Representative and collectively the Representatives). If any dispute arises with respect to either Owners performance under this Agreement that is not resolved by an independent engineer pursuant to provisions of Section 2.1(e), the Representatives shall meet to attempt to resolve such dispute, either in person or by telephone, within five (5) Business Days after the written request of either Representative. 11.1 Indemnification by Owners.
(a) Owner Indemnification. To the full extent permitted by Law, each Owner (an Indemnifying Owner) agrees to indemnify, defend and hold harmless each other Owner and the other Owners Affiliates and its and their respective directors, managers, officers, shareholders, partners, members, employees, contractors, agents and representatives (collectively, the Indemnified Parties), from and against any and all Liabilities, to the extent arising out of or related to (a) claims of any Person who is not an Owner or Indemnified Parties of an Owner to the extent they arise or result from, or are occasioned by or in connection with (i) any breach by the Owner of any of its obligations under this Agreement or (ii) any negligent, grossly negligent or willful misconduct in relation to the Common Facilities by the Owner or its Affiliates or its or their respective directors, managers, officers, shareholders, partners, members, employees, contractors, agents and representatives; or (b) any breach of this Agreement by the Owner. Should the Indemnified Party be entitled to indemnification under Section 11.1(a) as a result of a Claim by a third party, and the Indemnifying Owner fails to assume the defense of such Claim or fails to diligently pursue such Claim, the Indemnified Party may, at the expense of the Indemnifying Owner, contest (or, with the prior written consent of the Indemnifying Owner, settle) such Claim.
(d) Indemnification Amount. In the event that an Indemnifying Owner is obligated to indemnify and hold an Indemnified Party harmless under Section 11.1(a), the amount owing to the Indemnified Party shall be the amount of such Indemnified Party's reasonable, actual out-of-pocket Liabilities net of any insurance or other recovery actually received.
(e) Contribution. Except for indemnities, liabilities or obligations to be borne in a manner other than in accordance with Sharing Ratios pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, in the event that an Owner bears more than its applicable Sharing Ratio of any Liability or obligation arising in connection with the Common Facilities and such Owner would not be required to indemnify any other Owner for such liability or obligation pursuant to Sections 11.1(a) above (a Shared Liability), the other Owners shall reimburse the Owner that incurred the Shared Liability within ten (10) Business Days after written demand therefor, to the extent of such excess so that the Owners bear that liability or obligation in proportion to their respective Sharing Ratios. No Owner shall settle or compromise any claim with respect to a Shared Liability without the written approval of the other Owners.
(f) Payment. In computing the amount of any such tax cost or tax benefit, the actual combined federal and state tax rate applicable to the Indemnified Owner shall be used. The amount of any such tax benefit or tax cost that is deferred or will be realized over time (including, without limitation, depreciation or amortization deductions) shall be the net present value of the future benefits or costs, as applicable, using a discount rate equal to the mid- term applicable federal rate in effect on the day on which the related amounts are paid as indemnification under this Section 11.1.

ARTICLE 13 : MISCELLANEOUS
13.1 Recordation.
Upon full execution of this Agreement, the Parties shall execute and cause to be acknowledged a recordable memorandum of this Agreement substantially in the form of Exhibit G hereto (the Memorandum), which Memorandum shall promptly be recorded in the Office of the County Clerk of Somerset County, Pennsylvania, to the extent possible under governing law.
13.2 Several Obligations; Relationship of Parties.
The duties, obligations and liabilities of the Owners under this Agreement are intended to be several and not joint or collective. No Owner shall be jointly or severally liable under this Agreement for the acts, omissions or obligations of any other Owner, including, without limitation, any other Owners acts, omissions or obligations under such other Owners interconnection agreement, notwithstanding any provisions of such other Owners interconnection agreement to the contrary that are required to be included by the Transmission Provider for such Transmission Providers benefit. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express written consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement.
13.3 Regulatory Approvals and Assurances.
To the extent any regulatory approvals are required in connection with this Agreement, the Owners shall cooperate in connection with any and all filings and submissions for review, approval, permission to become effective or other authorization by the FERC or by any other entity having any regulatory jurisdiction over this Agreement. The Parties acknowledge and agree that (a) they shall seek acceptance by the FERC of this Agreement under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act; (b) any subsequent amendments to this Agreement that, pursuant to Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and FERC precedent thereunder, are required to be filed at FERC, must be accepted by FERC, and the effectiveness of such amendments will be contingent on such FERC acceptance; (c) changes in ownership contemplated by this Agreement may be subject to prior FERC approval pursuant to Section 203 of the Federal Power Act; and (d) disconnections or terminations contemplated by this Agreement may require prior FERC approval under the Federal Power Act. This Agreement shall become effective as of the date on which any required FERC or other entity with regulatory jurisdiction has approved, accepted for filing or permitted to become effective this Agreement without change or new condition (except for any change or new condition that is acceptable to each Owner).
13.4 Removal of Common Facilities from Service.
When all of the Owners direct the Administrative Owner to permanently remove the Common Facilities from service, the Administrative Owner shall dispose of the Common Facilities, or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, being removed from service. After deducting all costs of disposing of the Common Facilities, or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, including the cost of removing all structures and disposing of the debris and meeting all requirements of applicable law, the Administrative Owner shall distribute to each Owner a percentage of net proceeds from such disposition equal to the ratio of its Ownership Interest to the Ownership Interest of all Owners. In the event such costs of disposing of the Common Facilities, or of part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, pursuant to this Section 13.4, exceed the amount of the proceeds from the disposition of the Common Facilities or such part of the Common Facilities, each Owner shall pay a portion of excess costs related to the disposition of the Common Facilities or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, as such excess costs are incurred, equal to its Sharing Ratio. Administrative Owner will notify FristEnergy of any removal of Common Facilities from service thirty (30) calendar days prior to the removal date. The terms of this Section 13.4 shall survive the termination of this Agreement.
13.5 No Abandonment; Termination; Withdrawal. (a) No act or failure to act on the part of any Owner shall be deemed to constitute an abandonment of the Ownership Interest of such Owner, except in accordance with Section 13.5(b)(iii). The Term of this Agreement shall terminate, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, upon the first to occur of: (i) the failure of the first Sharing Effective Date for a Subsequent Project to occur as provided in Section 2.2(a)(ii), (ii) a single Owner becoming the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Common Facilities after the occurrence of the first Sharing Effective Date, or (iii) the mutual agreement of all the Owners. This Agreement shall only terminate or be terminated as provided in Section 2.2(a)(ii) or this Section 13.5.
(b) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Agreement, any Owner may elect to surrender its Ownership Interest and withdraw from this Agreement, but only with the consent of all of the Owners. The withdrawing Owner shall convey its Ownership Interest and assign its rights hereunder to the remaining Owner or Owners and, thereupon, the withdrawing Owner shall cease to have any right, title or interest in the Common Facilities or its Ownership Interest; provided that: (A) the withdrawing Owner executes and delivers all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect (and that do effect) the conveyance of its Ownership Interest and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Owner or Owners, (B) such assignment and conveyance is accompanied by an assignment by the withdrawing Owner to the remaining Owner or Owners of all its rights under this Agreement and (C) an encumbered Ownership Interest may only be surrendered with the written consent of each secured party that holds a security interest in such Ownership Interest and a release of such secured party's security interest therein. No surrender of an Owners Ownership Interest shall relieve the withdrawing Owner of any of its obligations under any agreement (including this Agreement and the obligation to pay its share of the Shared Expenses through the effective date of such surrender), unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or agreed in a writing among the Owners. After the Sharing Effective Date, in addition to the obligations of the withdrawing Owner set forth herein and in the event an Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Project, and the Ownership Interest of such Owner is not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the withdrawing Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the withdrawing Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owners of its intent to abandon its Project, be responsible for its proportionate share (as determined by such Owners Ownership Interest as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the Shared Premises as required by the Shared Real Property Documents (collectively, the Withdrawal Costs). The Administrative Owner shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows (provided, however, that if the Administrative Owner is the withdrawing Owner, then the non-withdrawing Owner(s) shall have the rights and perform the obligations of the Administrative Owner under this Section 13.5):
(i) The Administrative Owner shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the withdrawing Owner within forty-five (45) days after the Administrative Owner has received notice of Owners intent to abandon its Project.
(ii) The withdrawing Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs to the Administrative Owner. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained by the Administrative Owner in a reserve account and used by the Administrative Owner for removal of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the Shared Premises when same becomes necessary.
(iii) Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its Ownership Interest hereunder to the other Owners and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Common Facilities. The withdrawing Owner further irrevocably appoints the Administrative Owner as its true and lawful attorney, with full power of substitution, for the sole use and benefit of the remaining Owners, but at the withdrawing Owners expense, to the extent permitted by law to exercise, at any time and from time to time while the surrendering Owners default has occurred and is continuing, the power to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise deal in or with the Ownership Interest of the withdrawing Owner or the proceeds thereof, as fully and effectually as if the Administrative Owner were the absolute owner thereof, provided that the Administrative Owner shall give to the withdrawing Owner not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the time and place of a sale or other intended transfer or disposition of any of such Ownership Interest. Any Ownership Interest of the withdrawing Owner transferred or surrendered to the other Owners shall be allocated based on the Ownership Interests as recalculated in accordance with Section 2.2 after giving effect to such withdrawal, unless Casselman is no longer an Owner, in which case, such allocation shall be on a pro rata basis in accordance with each remaining Owners Ownership Interest.
13.6 Unavoidable Delays.
If any Party is delayed, hindered in or prevented from performing any act required under this Agreement by reason of strikes, lockouts, labor troubles, inability to procure materials, failure of power, restrictive governmental laws or regulations, natural disasters, war, terrorism, civil strife or other violence, the affected Party, upon giving notice to the other Party, shall be excused from performing the act (except payment of consideration) for the period of the delay. The affected Party shall use its reasonable efforts to avoid or remove the causes of nonperformance and shall continue performance whenever the causes for nonperformance are removed.
13.7 Run with the Land.
The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the real estate described in this Agreement and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon said real estate and each Partys present or future estate or interest therein and upon each of the Parties, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any lender or other person acquiring title from any such person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties and their respective successors and assigns and the real estate and any present or future holder of an estate or interest therein. To the extent any of the provisions of this Agreement are not enforceable as covenants running with the land, they shall be enforceable as equitable servitudes.
13.8 Certifications.
Each Party shall, upon not less than ten (10) days prior written notice from time to time given by any other Party or by any existing or proposed lender, assignee, subgrantee or equity investor with respect to a Party (each, a Requesting Party), execute, acknowledge and deliver to the Requesting Party a written statement (a) certifying that the Grants and this Agreement are unmodified and in full force and effect (or, if modified, stating the nature of such modification and certifying that the Grants and this Agreement, as so modified, are in full force and effect), and (b) certifying that there are not, to the non-requesting Partys knowledge, any uncured defaults hereunder, or describing with particularity each such uncured default if any are claimed. Any such statements may be conclusively relied upon by the Requesting Party. The failure of the non-requesting Party to deliver any such statement within such time shall be conclusive upon such non-requesting Party that (i) the Grants and this Agreement are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (ii) there are no uncured defaults hereunder.
13.9 Partition Waiver.
The Owners agree that neither the Common Facilities nor the Shared Premises are suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under applicable law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Common Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Common Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Section 13.4 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights.
13.10 Entire Agreement/Amendments.
This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with regard to its subject matter. This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties.
13.11 Further Assurances.
The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably needed by the Parties for their business purposes so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement.
13.12 Choice of Law.
This Agreement shall be deemed made and prepared and shall be construed and interpreted in accordance with the internal laws of the State of New York, without regard to principles of conflicts of law thereof that may require the application of the law of another jurisdiction (other than Sections 5-1401 and 5-1402 of the New York General Obligations Law); provided, that the Laws of the State of Pennsylvania shall be applicable to and govern matters relating to real property, including without limitation, marketability of title, the creation, nature or transfer of an interest in, or liens attaching to, real property or the manner and effect of recording or failing to record evidence of an interest in or lien on real property.
13.13 Time of Essence.
Time is of the essence with regard to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
13.14 Partial Invalidity.
Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall the Term be for longer periods than the longest periods permitted by applicable law.
13.15 Approvals.
No approval required by this Agreement shall be unreasonably withheld or delayed. Unless a longer or shorter time is specified, all approvals required of either Party shall be given or refused in writing within ten (10) Business Days after receipt of the request for approval. Any delay of a requested approval longer than ten (10) Business Days shall be deemed an approval. Approvals shall not be unreasonably withheld except in instances where this Agreement specifically permits a Party to act in its sole discretion.
13.16 As-Is Condition.
The Grants are granted and conveyed to each Subsequent Party subject to the present or future condition of the Shared Premises and AS-IS, WHERE-IS, with all faults, and each Subsequent Party hereby accepts the Grants and such Shared Premises in such condition and on such basis. Each Subsequent Party acknowledges that for purposes of this Agreement, neither Casselman nor any of its representatives or agents has made any representation or warranty as to the suitability of the Shared Premises or any portion thereof for the conduct of operations or for any other purpose.
13.17 Cooperation.
Each Party shall reasonably support and cooperate with each other Party in the conduct of its operations and the exercise of its rights hereunder, and in carrying out and otherwise giving full force and effect to the purpose and intent of this Agreement, including in a Partys efforts to obtain from any governmental authority or any other Person any permit, entitlement, approval, authorization or other rights necessary or convenient in connection with its operations and/or the exercise of its rights hereunder; and each Party shall, without demanding additional consideration therefor, promptly execute, and, if appropriate, cause to be acknowledged and recorded, any map, application, document or instrument that is reasonably requested by any other Party or any governmental authority in connection therewith.
13.18 Attornment.
If any other Person shall succeed to all of a Partys interests in the Shared Premises, this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect as a direct agreement between the then owner of such Partys interests in the Shared Premises and the other Party, upon and subject to all of the terms, covenants and conditions herein for the remaining balance of the term hereof, and the other Party does hereby attorn to such new holder, such attornment to be effective and self-operating without the execution of any further instruments.
13.19 No Third Party Beneficiaries.
Except with respect to the rights of Lenders as stated above, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto, and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not a Party to this Agreement.
13.20 Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts.
This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby. This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts, all of which shall constitute one and the same Agreement.

physically and separately measure the output from the Casselman Wind Project and the Summit Solar Project in order to appropriately allocate revenues from such output to such Projects, (3) the shared use of various other Common Facilities, for the mutual benefit of the Casselman Wind Project, Summit Solar Project, and additional Subsequent Project(s), as well as various related rights and responsibilities, and (4) the terms and conditions for the Summit Solar Project and other Subsequent Projects (as defined in the Agreement) to join the Agreement for purposes of sharing in the use of the Common Facilities.
B. Capitalized terms used in this Memorandum and not otherwise defined have the same meanings ascribed to such terms in the Agreement.
AGREEMENT
NOW, THEREFORE, Casselman and Aurora hereby provide constructive and public notice of the Agreement and certain terms thereof as follows:
1. Common Facilities and Shared Premises. The Agreement contains terms for the joinder of Subsequent Parties and interconnection of any Subsequent Project and construction and installation of any Additional Common Facilities. Pursuant to the Agreement, with respect to each Subsequent Project for which the Sharing Effective Date has occurred, Casselman and the Subsequent Party owning such Subsequent Project, agree to jointly own and use the Common Facilities and Shared Premises, on and subject to the terms and conditions set forth in the Agreement. For each Subsequent Project to be constructed under the Agreement, the Subsequent Party shall include in the Interconnection Plans detailed depictions of each area of the Casselman Wind Land proposed to be included as Shared Premises. The potential Shared Real Property Documents covering potential Shared Premises include those documents listed on Exhibit B attached hereto. Pursuant to the terms of the Agreement, the Parties may enter into an amendment or supplement to the Agreement (and this Memorandum, as the Parties may determine) upon satisfaction of the Casselman Land Use Condition by each Subsequent Project to add as Shared Real Property Documents the Casselman Real Property Interests which satisfy the Casselman Land Use Condition as confirmed by Casselman. If the Sharing Effective Date has not occurred for the first Subsequent Project within ten (10) years after the Effective Date, the Agreement shall automatically terminate and be of no further force and effect.
2. Conveyances of Undivided Interests. Effective as of the Sharing Effective Date for any Subsequent Project, the Agreement provides for the conveyance of undivided interest(s) to the Subsequent Party owning such Subsequent Project in and to the Common Facilities and its Shared Interests under the Shared Real Property Documents. As confirmation of the occurrence of such conveyances, upon satisfaction of the terms and conditions set forth in the Agreement therefor, the applicable Parties shall execute and record such additional Shared Interest Conveyance Documents as may reasonably be requested by any Party to further evidence such conveyances, for recording in the real property records.
3. Restrictions on Transfer. No Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its Ownership Interest or other rights or interests in or to the Common Facilities, or in, to or under the Agreement except in accordance with the terms of the Agreement. Any attempted or

purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Common Facilities or the Agreement made other than in accordance with the terms of the Agreement either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect.
4. Covenant Running with the Land. Each obligation of the Parties under the Agreement is a covenant running with the land and will inure to the benefit of and be binding upon, as applicable, the successors and assigns of the Parties, with respect to all such Persons respective interests in the real property subject to the Agreement. This Memorandum shall automatically terminate and be of no force or effect upon any termination of the Common Facilities Agreement.
5. Conflict. In the event of any conflict or inconsistency between the provisions of this Memorandum and the provisions of the Agreement, the provisions of the Agreement shall control. Nothing in this Memorandum shall be deemed to amend, modify, change, alter, amplify, limit, interpret or supersede any provision of the Agreement or otherwise limit or expand the rights and obligations of the parties under the Agreement, and the Agreement shall control over this Memorandum in all events.
6. Counterparts. This Memorandum may be executed with counterpart signature pages and in duplicate originals, each of which shall be deemed an original, and all of which together shall constitute a single instrument.
